	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Fennyin,<br><br>I believe this information is based on the Copeland's Weapon Analyzer so it is pre-Damage Bonus patch. However, my understanding of the Damage Bonus Patch is that damage bonuses were assigned based on the weapon's current damage and delay. Most of these weapons should have improved propotionately to where there's no big order swing on the list...just a few adjustments to overall damage per minute...with the exception, perhaps, of the Nathsar Greatsword.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Nathsar Greatsword...which scores so high on the list because it's fast...not because it has big damage may not have faired so well with the patch.  I would suspect that if anything, it would DROP in the rankings post-patch since I doubt it got a big Damage Bonus adjustment due to it's fast delay.  That's speculation. Someone who has one correct me if I'm wrong!<br><br>I picked this information up at the &quot;Paladins of Everquest&quot; site.  If I knew how to do one of those fancy hot-links, I would, but I don't, so here it is the hard way!<br><br><a href="http://trump9.tripod.com/paladin.html" target=_new>http://trump9.tripod.com/paladin.html</a><br><br>Good Luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
